(reuters.com, 06 Dec 2017)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralSANCTIONSIn 2009 he tested positive for the prohibited substance metandienone during an out-of-competition test. In 2011 the Court of Arbitration for Sport [CAS] reduced the ban to 12 years, after accepting his first offence had been the result of a coach doping Iranian weightlifters without their knowledge. Ali Hosseini then made a second successful appeal and his suspension was cut to eight years. He became eligible to return to competition in October 2017. (mojnews.com, 23 Oct 2017; iwf.net, 01 Oct 2017; espn.co.uk, 26 Oct 2011) '), ('Hero', 'US sprinter Justin Gatlin. bio: [('Beginning', 'He took up discus at age 16. (iaaf.org, 05 Jun 2008)'), ('Reason', 'He took aim at goal in a school handball match and threw the ball with such power it broke the goalpost. His surprised sports teacher told him he had to take part in a throwing sport. "I have always loved throwing ever since I was a child. Even when we went to the Caspian Sea, I threw rocks into the sea." (thestar.com.my, 27 Jul 2008)'), ('Coach', 'Mac Wilkins [personal], USA (usatf.org, 09 May 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. (tasnimnews.com, 12 Aug 2016)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralNATIONAL FIRSTSHe became the first Iranian to win a medal in athletics at the Olympic Games, when he took silver in discus at the 2012 Games in London. He was also the first Iranian to win a medal at the world championships, following his bronze medal in discus at the 2011 edition in Daegu, Republic of Korea. (presstv.ir, 07 Aug 2012; parsherald.com, 20 Apr 2013; SportsDeskOnline, 16 May 2018)EARLY YEARSHe quit the sport in his youth after not being selected for the national school championships in Iran. He returned to the sport four years later when a coach noticed his physical attributes at an athletics competition he attended as a spectator. "I remember as if it were now when a coach came to me, asked me to stand up and measured my height and arm span, keeping silent. Then he said that I can be a good discus thrower and invited me to his group." (iaaf.org, 17 Jul 2012) '), ('Injuries', 'His performance was hindered by injury at the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. He underwent three surgeries on his left knee and heel following the Games and was unable to walk for three months. (tasnimnews.com, 12 Aug 2016; sportstarlive.com, 07 Jul 2017)'), ('Languages', 'English, Farsi, Russian'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationResultAsian Games1Discus Throw2014Incheon, KOR65.111Discus Throw2010Guangzhou, CHN67.991Discus Throw2006Doha, QAT63.79Olympic Games2Discus Throw2012London, GBR68.18QualificationDiscus Throw2016Rio de Janeiro, BRA60.15QualificationDiscus Throw2008Beijing, CHN61.34World Championships3Discus Throw2011Daegu, KOR66.087Discus Throw2007Osaka, JPN64.53QualificationDiscus Throw2017London, GBR63.03QualificationDiscus Throw2015Beijing, CHN60.39Diamond League2Discus Throw2018Oslo, NOR67.553Discus Throw2018Stockholm, SWE67.683Discus Throw2018Rome, ITA65.936Discus Throw2018Paris Saint-Denis, FRA64.366Discus Throw2015Oslo, NOR60.466Discus Throw2015Eugene, OR, USA61.67World Challenge3Discus Throw2016Madrid, ESP63.105Discus Throw2018Ostrava, CZE64.45Asian Championships1Discus Throw2017Bhubaneswar, IND64.541Discus Throw2011Kobe, JPN62.271Discus Throw2009Guangzhou, CHN64.831Discus Throw2007Amman, JOR65.38NMDiscus Throw2015Wuhan, CHNNM')]

name: Saeedreza
bio: [('Additional Information', "GeneralNAMED ELEMENTSIn July 2017 the International Gymnastics Federation [FIG] named a pommel horse element after him. The element will be known as the 'Keikha 2' and was first performed successfully at the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games in Baku, Azerbaijan. He previously had an element on the pommel horse known as the 'Keikha' named after him in March 2017. He is the first Iranian athlete to have an element named after him. name: ZAHRA
bio: [('Beginning', 'She took up archery in 2007, about three years after she sustained a spinal cord injury when she was hit by a car. (theguardian.com, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (tehrantimes.com, 05 Sep 2017)'), ('Awards', 'She was named the 2017 Athlete of the Year by World Archery. (tasmimnews.com, 22 Feb 2018)She was flag bearer for the Islamic Republic of Iran at the opening ceremony of the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. (indianexpress.com, 10 Aug 2016)In November 2015 she was named the International Paralympic Committee [IPC] Athlete of the Month. (worldarchery.org, 25 Jan 2016)She was presented with the Spirit of Sport Individual Award at the 2013 SportAccord Convention in St. Petersburg, Russian Federation. (archery.org, 30 May 2013)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralSPINAL INJURYShe uses a wheelchair after sustaining a serious spinal injury at age 18 when she was hit by a car. Ashe was a black belt in taekwondo before the incident, and took up archery in 2007. "Archery made me strong - and taught me the meaning of strength. When I was 18 I lost the ability to walk in a car accident. I was close to losing my life. But I had a chance to live." (theguardian.com, 09 Aug 2016)NATIONAL FIRSTSShe is the first athlete from the Islamic Republic of Iran to have competed at both the Paralympic Games and the Olympic Games. She competed in archery at the Paralympic Games in 2012 and 2016, and at the Olympic Games in 2016. She was also the first archer from the Islamic Republic of Iran to win gold at the Paralympic Games, claiming gold in women\'s individual recurve at the 2012 Games in London. (SportsDeskOnline, 30 Jul 2018; varzesh3.com, 25 Nov 2015)OTHER ACTIVITIESShe has served as an ambassador for the United Nations for her role in empowering women through sport. (worldarchery.org, 25 Jan 2016) '), ('Injuries', 'She sustained a hand injury in 2017. name: KIANOUSH
bio: [('Beginning', 'He began weightlifting at age 10. (bellsofsteel.com, 05 Jan 2015)'), ('Reason', 'He initially took part in gymnastics, but he also started weight training with his brother who encouraged him to switch sports. "My brother trained in weightlifting with me and told me, \'You\'re coming weightlifting instead\'." (bellsofsteel.com, 05 Jan 2015)'), ('Coach', 'Kourosh Rstami [personal, brother], IRI (donya-e-eqtesad.com, 04 Dec 2017)'), ('Training', 'Since before the 2016 Olympic Games In Rio de Janeiro, he has trained alone, away from the national training setup. (insidethegames.biz, 07 Mar 2018; donya-e-eqtesad.com, 04 Dec 2017)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (alef.ir, 01 Jul 2018)'), ('Awards', 'He was named 2016 Male Lifter of the Year by the International Weightlifting Federation [IWF]. (barbend.com, 07 Feb 2017)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralWEIGHT CHANGEIn July 2018 he decided to change from the 85kg weight class up to 94kg in preparation for the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. "I wanted a new challenge. For eight years, I was the best athlete in the 85kg category and I would like to show myself that I can succeed at another weight." (alef.ir, 01 Jul 2018)AUCTIONIn November 2017 he announced he would auction the gold medal he won in the 85kg category at the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro, and use the proceeds to help people affected by an earthquake that month in Islamic Republic of Iran. "I consider it my duty to take a step, however small, to help my beloved fellow countrymen who have suffered as a result of the quake. I am returning the gold medal, which is theirs by right, to my people." (Instagram profile, 14 Nov 2017; edition.cnn.com, 14 Nov 2017)DROPPEDIn early 2017 he was dropped by coach Sajjad Anoushiravani from the national team for the 2017 Asian Championships in Ashgabat, Turkmenistan, and the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games in Baku, Azerbaijan, for not participating in training. Rostami said he did not compete in the events because he was resting for a year following the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro. "I don\'t have any problems with the Iran Weightlifting Federation but my training programme, the way I use my time, is different to all others, it\'s my own." He rejoined the national team ahead of the 2017 World Championships in Anaheim, CA, United States of America. (insidethegames.biz, 05 Nov 2017; floelite.com, 15 Nov 2017; barbend.com, 06 Feb 2017) '), ('Injuries', 'He was troubled by a knee injury at the 2017 World Championships in Anaheim, CA, United States of America.
